    {
        "name": "Getting the website running",
        "chapters": [
            {
                "blockname": "New Block 1",
                "name": "Introduction",
                "sections": [
                    {
                        "subtitle": "Learning Outcomes",
                        "space_after": false,
                        "components": [
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "text": "In this chapter, you will do all the necessary work to upload and start your website on your heroku server."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "list-text",
                                "list_elements": [
                                    {
                                        "links": [],
                                        "text": "Learn how to fork a repository on Github."
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "links": [],
                                        "text": "Learn how to link your github repository to your heroku app."
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "links": [],
                                        "text": "Learn how to deploy your website using heroku."
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "blockname": "Getting the website",
                "name": "Using github",
                "sections": [
                    {
                        "subtitle": "Fork the website repository",
                        "space_after": false,
                        "components": [
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "text": "In github, every user can have repositories. These can be private and public. A repository is a collection of files, that is stored on the cloud. Github also comes with a version control system, meaning that the state of your files is saved between changes. This means that you can see previous versions of your files after you have made changes. In our context, this can be useful if you have made mistakes when editing the content of the website and want to revert back to a previous state."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [
                                    {
                                        "href": "https://help.github.com/articles/fork-a-repo/",
                                        "portion": "forking a repository"
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "portion": "You can find it here",
                                        "href": "https://github.com/ovidium19/SupportForStudents"
                                    }
                                ],
                                "text": "This website is available in the format of a github repository. You can find it here. In order to continue at this point, you need to get a copy of this repository into your own github account. In order to do that, there is a process in github called forking a repository.",
                                "space_after": true
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [
                                    {
                                        "portion": "this repository",
                                        "href": "https://github.com/ovidium19/SupportForStudents"
                                    }
                                ],
                                "text": "In order to complete this step, you need to fork a copy of the website template page into your own github account. Simply go to this repository and click the 'Fork' button on the top-right side. This process will take several seconds, and then you will end up with a repository in your github account that has the name 'ifs-template-website'."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "blockname": "Getting the website",
                "name": "Using heroku",
                "sections": [
                    {
                        "subtitle": "Using heroku",
                        "space_after": false,
                        "components": [
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "text": "You now have a repository in your github account called 'ifs-template-website'. Congratulations!!"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "text": "The next step is letting our heroku app know where our repository is."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "list-text",
                                "list_elements": [
                                    {
                                        "links": [
                                            {
                                                "portion": "dashboard",
                                                "href": "https://dashboard.heroku.com/apps"
                                            }
                                        ],
                                        "text": "Go to your dashboard and select the previously created heroku app."
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "links": [],
                                        "text": "Go to the 'Deploy' tab"
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "image-single",
                                "src": "images/heroku_deplymenu.jpg"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "list-text",
                                "list_elements": [
                                    {
                                        "links": [],
                                        "text": "Where it says 'Deployment Method', click on Github."
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "links": [],
                                        "text": "Below that, there is a form with the title 'Search for a repository to connect to'. Start typing the name of your repository, which should be 'ifs-template-website' if you haven't changed the name."
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "image-single",
                                "src": "images/heroku_gitdeploy.jpg"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "list-text",
                                "list_elements": [
                                    {
                                        "links": [],
                                        "text": "Once you click 'Search', the results will show just below. Click 'Connect' on the search result that pops up."
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "links": [],
                                        "text": "After you connect the repository to heroku, more options will appear on the screen. You don't have to worry about these. Simply scroll all the way down to the section labelled 'Manual Deploy' and then click the button 'Deploy Branch'."
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "links": [],
                                        "text": "After you click the button, the repository is copied on the heroku server. This takes some time, but you are provided feedback in the logs below. Once this process is done, another button will pop up , the 'View' button. Clicking this will take you to your new website."
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "blockname": "Getting the website running",
                "name": "Summary",
                "sections": [
                    {
                        "subtitle": "Congratulations",
                        "space_after": false,
                        "components": [
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "text": "You have done a lot of work in this chapter, and you now have a brand new website ready and deployed. It is time now to take a look at how to protect its admin features so that you are the only one that can access them. Let's talk about Authentication."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
