                    {
                        "subtitle": "Introduction",
                        "space_after": false,
                        "components": [
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "text": "In this chapter, I will go over the admin page, its structure and elements and try to get you familiar with all the various components that are available, how to add and remove them."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "subtitle": "Learning Outcomes",
                        "space_after": false,
                        "components": [
                            {
                                "type": "list-text",
                                "list_elements": [
                                    {
                                        "links": [],
                                        "text": "Learn the terminology."
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "links": [],
                                        "text": "Explore the various widgets and buttons available on the admin page."
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "links": [],
                                        "text": "Explore the Undo queue and learn how to correct mistakes."
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "links": [],
                                        "text": "Learn how to add and remove elements."
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "links": [],
                                        "text": "Explore the available components in small detail."
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "blockname": "Admin Primer",
                "name": "Getting to grips with page structure",
                "sections": [
                    {
                        "subtitle": "Terminology",
                        "space_after": true,
                        "components": [
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "subtitle": "Blocks",
                                "text": "Blocks are the main elements of your data. They encapsulate all chapters and are available in the navigation menu on the left. The blocks in this case are: Introduction, Getting the website running, Authentication etc."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "text": "Blocks are made of chapters.",
                                "space_after": true
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "subtitle": "Chapters",
                                "text": "Chapters are the containers inside a block. For example, the chapters for the 'Admin Primer' block are : Introduction, Getting to grips with page structure, Adding and removing elements, etc.",
                                "space_after": true
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "space_after": true,
                                "subtitle": "Sections",
                                "text": "Each page is made of several sections. A section starts with a coloured title. Sections also appear on the right side navigation menu for quick navigation. The sections on this page are: Terminology, Menus, Widgets, Form Page"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text-alert",
                                "text": "It is good practice to give your Blocks, Chapters and Sections very relevant names, as they appear in navigation menus and allow the user to quickly navigate to what they are looking for",
                                "space_after": true
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "subtitle": "Components",
                                "text": "Everything else is a component. All paragraphs, images, videos, alerts, links are components. When you create a page, it will usually be several sections which contain several components. We will go over components more in a later chapter."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "subtitle": "Menus",
                        "space_after": true,
                        "components": [
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "text": "The main menu on the left contains all the Blocks and Chapters, while the menu on the right will display all sections on the currently selected Block+Chapter."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "text": "Notice that when you select a Block, it will automatically select the first Chapter from it. A block cannot contain anything else besides Chapters."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "text": "All Blocks, Chapters and Sections must have a name. Name is optional for components."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text-alert",
                                "text": "When you edit the content, you must always have at least 1 Block with 1 Chapter. The website will not let you delete content if you have less than required."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "subtitle": "Widgets",
                        "space_after": true,
                        "components": [
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "text": "You can notice many buttons on the admin page. Everything in here is editable, therefore there are many ways you can interact with your blocks, chapters, sections and components."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "subtitle": "The Add Buttons",
                                "space_after": false,
                                "text": "There are 4 different Add buttons available. You can add Blocks and Chapters from the menu on the left. You can add Sections to a Page through the Add Section button at the bottom of the page, or the Add New Section button on the right-side menu."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "space_after": true,
                                "text": "You can add components with the Add Component button. Since components must belong to a Section, every Section comes equipped with this button at the bottom of the Section."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "subtitle": "The Colored Borders",
                                "text": "There are coloured borders displayed for Sections and Components. Sections have a blue border, and Components have a red border. This is so you can easily identify which component and section you are currently editing."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "text": "Notice that components(red borders) are encapsulated in sections(blue borders). You must understand this hierarchy before proceeding forward."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text-alert",
                                "text": "Blocks contain chapters, which contain sections, which contain components.",
                                "space_after": true
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "subtitle": "The Collapse Button",
                                "space_after": true,
                                "text": "Sections and Components can get fairly big in size, making it hard to navigate your page. These two elements come equipped with a Collapse button at the beginning. Clicking this will collapse the contents of the element, making the page shorter. It is good practice to collapse Sections that you have finished editing, and only leave the Section you are currently working on uncollapsed."
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text-paragraph",
                                "links": [],
                                "subtitle": "Move and Delete Widgets",
                                "space_after": true,
                                "text": "Every element has these widgets. It's a group of three buttons that can move the element up or down in the hierarchy, or delete it. You can easily change the order of your elements with these buttons, or delete an element. You will be prompted to accept when you try to delete something."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
